<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12033l"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12033l">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12033l"> 33(l)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> if Jeremy was, as he was &mdash;</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><mark>If the Prophet Jeremias was sanctified, as he was,</mark> in his mother&apos;s womb, because his heavenly mission was to announce to the world the mysteries and revelations of the Almighty; if St. John the Baptist was sanctified, as he was, before he was born, because he was destined to baptize the Saviour of the world, to point out the Redeemer in person, &ldquo;Behold the Lamb of God;&rdquo; if these Saints were holy because they approached near God, and were destined to fulfill a high and holy mission; what special unique privileges, graces, and favours must not the Almighty have reserved for our Blessed Lady, &hellip; <small> Very Rev. Dean Kinane, <a name="TKSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TKSP"><cite title="source">St. Patrick: his life, his heroic virtues, his labours, and the fruits of his labours</cite></a>, (ed. unknown) 2-3</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12018e" href="c12all.htm#c12018e">VI.C.12:018(e)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
